This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as entity typing. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an end-to-end neural model for the task. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques to solve a complex problem. It may also be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as entity typing is a crucial task in information retrieval systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a neural model for the task.
